[SN]TITLE[SN]
Nice 1-0 Rennes

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Nice wore a commemorative kit in their opening Ligue 1 fixture of the season in tribute to the 85 people killed when an attacker drove a lorry into a crowd in the city.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Those killed were celebrating Bastille Day, France's national day, on 14 July.
All the names of the victims were printed on the middle of the white shirts in a heart shape for Sunday's game, which Nice won 1-0.
There were no sponsors on the shirts despite ongoing contractual agreements.
